{"article_id":"z2xNUPbseehTHszy","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Judge Brett Kavanaugh 's nomination","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"to be the next Supreme Court justice","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"will be decided Thursday .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"All 100 senators will be able to review the supplemental background investigation throughout the day .","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"A reminder","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"that barring some dramatic disclosure in from that inquiry ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"96 senators have already made up their minds .","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"How the remaining groups sees the new background information","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"-- and how it factors into their decisions --","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"will drive the day .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"It all comes down to five senators","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"-- three Republicans and two Democrats --","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"and what they see today behind closed doors .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Here are the rules","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"senators are following","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"to review the documents .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Judiciary Committee Republican staff got the first look at the FBI 's findings","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"starting at 8 a.m . ET .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"At 9 a.m . ET , Democrats took over the room .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Control of the room is scheduled to rotate , every other hour , for the rest of Thursday .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"The staff","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"that is cleared","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"to review the material","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"will provide briefings , likely to groups of senators ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"and the senators will be able to review the raw 302s themselves .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"Sen. Ron Johnson , a Republican from Wisconsin , told reporters","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"that staff from the office of Senate Judiciary Chairman Chuck Grassley are reading the report aloud to senators","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"and then other interviews","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"( that are n't being read aloud )","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"are being passed around for senators to look at .","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"There is only one copy ,","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"which is making things interesting .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"`` We are trying to get it all done efficiently , ''","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"Johnson said .","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"This FBI 's work is not public .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"It will likely never be public .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"There will be no summary .","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"There will be no release .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"There are 109 people","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"who have clearance","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"to access what was delivered to Capitol Hill at 2:30 Thursday morning","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"-- 100 senators , four majority committee staffers and four minority committee staffers , one committee clerk .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"That 's it .","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"There is a single copy of the FBI 's findings .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"It is currently in a vault , in a Sensitive Compartmented Information Facility","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"-- or SCIF ,","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"if you 'd like to use the Washington short hand .","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"It can not leave the room .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"Senators ca n't bring their phones into the SCIF","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"when they go to review the documents .","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"If they take notes ,","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"the notes must be left in the room","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"when the senator leaves .","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"Senators are not allowed to discuss or characterize in detail what they 've read","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"( though they most certainly will try . )","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"Johnson told reporters","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"that in the SCIF , there are little stands with microphones ,","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"where the judiciary staff is `` somewhat taking turns ''","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"briefing lawmakers from the FBI report .","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"`` I 've never seen anything like that before , ''","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"Johnson told reporters .","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"`` This is unusual circumstances","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"calling for kind of ( an ) unusual process . ''","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"Johnson said","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"the staff will stay","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"as long as people want to come read the report .","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"`` There is discussion too .","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"There are questions","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"being answered , ''","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"Johnson said .","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"`` I personally find it to be a pretty good , pretty efficient process . ''","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"The public is expected to only be able to gauge what 's in the FBI 's findings in two ways :","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"First :","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"the topline characterizations of senators","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"who read the documents .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"Reminder","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"these senators have very specific motivations for how they characterize what they see ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"especially given it wo n't be publicly released .","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"Second :","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"By the votes on the Senate floor .","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"If the undecided senators all get to `` yes , ''","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"then they saw something","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"that assuaged their concerns","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"-- or at least did n't create any more .","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"This is , quite literally , how the process is designed to work ,","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"as guided by a bipartisan Judiciary Committee memorandum of understanding","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"signed in 2009 .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"Background investigations are not supposed to be made public","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"-- in fact , it 's against the law to do so .","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"The limited number of people with access , the restrictions on public disclosure , even the number of copies","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"provided , are all dictated by rules","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"the committee agreed to nine years ago .","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"It 's worth noting --","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Republican senators discussed for days","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"whether there was a way","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"to make some form of the information public , either in summary form or some other mechanism .","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"It was decided","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"given the rules in place , and the potential legal issues ,","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"it is n't doable at this point .","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"The White House has explored ways","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"to make some of the FBI report public ,","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"an official familiar with the deliberations says ,","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"but lawyers have determined","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"it would be very difficult","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"without violating the Privacy Act or the memorandum of understanding","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"that dictates how the information is shared .","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"Officials feel","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"if the report was made public","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"it would prove the `` no corroboration '' line","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"they and Senate Republicans have been projecting this morning .","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"But as of Thursday morning , they believe","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"there is very little","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"they will be able to make public , or comment on specifically .","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"Separately , a senior White House official told CNN","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"they wo n't call for the release of the background investigation","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"- and claims","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"the Senate ca n't release it either .","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"Multiple senior GOP aides expressed confidence Wednesday night","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"that Kavanaugh was on the path to confirmation","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"-- though all acknowledged","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell still has n't received any commitments or assurances from the undecided senators .","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"The expectation ,","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"aides say ,","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"is barring some significant new disclosure in the FBI inquiry ,","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"they 'll make it over the vote threshold","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"to get Kavanaugh confirmed .","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"`` We 've made sure","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"they got what they needed , ''","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"one of the aides said .","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"`` Now we move forward . ''","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"The week-long delay is almost over .","depth":3},{"id":133,"text":"The FBI supplemental background check is officially on Capitol Hill .","depth":5},{"id":134,"text":"The first vote is scheduled for Friday .","depth":5},{"id":135,"text":"This is moving ,","depth":5},{"id":136,"text":"one way or another .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":273,"left":0,"right":272,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":272,"left":267,"right":271,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":267,"left":207,"right":266,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{